24/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Three Romanian journalists who were held hostage in Iraq returned to Bucharest on Monday (23 May).
They were welcomed at the airport by relatives and President Traian Basescu, who co-ordinated efforts for their release.
The three were taken to an unspecified location for medical tests and a debriefing.
Their translator, Mohamad Munaf, an Iraqi man who holds Romanian and US citizenship, was also released.
(Reuters, Nine o'clock, Rompres, Romanian Government Web site, Council of Europe Web site - 23/05/05)
